 'Are you a real pilot?'
 An old gentleman wearing a beat-up old leather flying jacket sat down at t=
he
Starbucks and ordered a cup of coffee.
=20
 As he sat sipping his coffee, a young woman sat down next to him...
=20
 She turned to the man and asked, 'Are you a real pilot?'
=20
 He replied, 'Well, I've spent my whole life flying; biplanes, Cubs,
Aeronca's,T-6s, flew in WWII in a B-25, and later Sabre jets in the Korean
conflict. I taught 50 people to fly and gave rides to hundreds, so yes, I
guess
I am a pilot.'
=20
 She said, 'I'm a lesbian. I spend my whole day thinking about naked women.=
 As
soon as I get up in the morning, I think about naked women. When I shower, I
think about naked women. When I watch TV, I think about naked women. It see=
ms
everything makes me think of naked women.'
=20
 The two sat sipping in silence.
=20
 A little while later, a young man sat down on the other side of the old pi=
lot
and asked, 'Are you a real pilot?'
=20
 He replied, 'I always thought I was, but I just found out that I'm a
lesbian.'
