</font><font size=3D"3" face=3D"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b>'Are=20
            you a real pilot?'<br>
            </b>An old gentleman wearing a beat-up old leather flying
jacket sat=20
            down at the Starbucks and ordered a cup of coffee.<br>
            <br>
            As he sat sipping his coffee, a young woman sat down next to
him...<br>
            <br>
            She turned to the man and asked, 'Are you a real=20
pilot?'<br>
            <br>
            He replied, 'Well, I've spent my whole life flying; biplanes,
Cubs,=20
            Aeronca's,T-6s, flew in WWII in a B-25, and later Sabre jets
in the=20
            Korean conflict. I taught 50 people to fly and gave rides to
hundreds,=20
            so yes, I guess I am a pilot.'<br>
            <br>
            She said, 'I'm a lesbian. I spend my whole day thinking about
naked=20
            women. As soon as I get up in the morning, I think about
naked women.=20
            When I shower, I think about naked women. When I watch TV, I
think=20
            about naked women. It seems everything makes me think of
naked women.'<br>
            <br>
            The two sat sipping in silence.<br>
            <br>
            A little while later, a young man sat down on the other side
of the=20
            old pilot and asked, 'Are you a real pilot?'<br>
            <br>
            He replied, 'I always thought I was, but I just found out
that I'm=20
            a lesbian.'<br>
